classification.tableDescription: 1980 Commissioners Standard Ordinary (CSO) Selection Factors – Male. Minimum Select Age: 0. Maximum Select Age: 65 and over.
classification.comments: Study Data: Society of Actuary (SOA) 1970-75 intercompany medical mortality data. Development of Tables K(M) and K(F) excluded the first five policy years of experience except for ages 0-4. In determining deficiency reserves, the absence of this data could result in strain on certain renewable term insurance plans priced on the basis of select mortality experience. Hence the Committee felt it would be reasonably conservative to develop ten-year selection factors to be used with the K Tables. The K tables were ultimately adopted as the 1980 Commissioners Standard Ordinary Tables (See SOA Table Identities 17 and 20). Methodology: Margins in Tables K(M) and K(F) were added to the crude select mortality rates from the 1970-75 intercompany medical data at central ages. Resulting loaded rates were divided by the appropriate Table K central age rates. Selection factors were modified to eliminate random fluctuations and then smoothed by an unspecified method so as to produce select mortality rates that increased with age. NOTE: For policy years 11 and over the selection factor is always 100%. Data Transcription Errors: None. Data Certified: 03/2013
